article.headline: Stetson 93, Colorado State 57
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. (AP) -- Matt Nelson scored 19 points on 7-for-7 shooting as Colorado State remained unbeaten at home with a 93-57 victory over Stetson Tuesday night. Nelson, who is shooting 77 percent over his last six games, also had eight rebounds. Nick Ball and Jon Rakiecki added 11 points each for Colorado State (7-4), as the Rams improved to 7-0 at home. Anthony Register, 10-for-11 on free throws, led Stetson (2-6) with 18 points. Boris Djordjic had 13 points and E.J. Gordon 12 for the Hatters who lost their fourth straight. Stetson stayed within striking distance in the first half by slowing the pace and getting seven points each from Djordjic and Register. But Colorado State began working the ball to the 7-foot Nelson for two baby hooks to cap a 9-2 run in the final two minutes of the first half. Nelson scored 14 as Colorado State took a 39-24 lead into the break. Nelson's two free throws at 9:32 remaining were his last points before retiring for the night with Colorado State ahead 67-36. Stetson was 0-for-10 on 3-pointers, the first time in 170 games they failed to hit a 3-point shot.
